    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 1974 the Alva Garden Club converted the former library into a museum, preserving artifacts from the town’s founding families.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alva%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Alva sits on the Caloosahatchee River, which flows westward through the community toward the Gulf of Mexico.",
